The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Shabbir free to bowl

Karachi: Pakistani paceman Shabbir Ahmed will be allowed to resume his international career after serving out a one-year ban for an illegal action, a PCB official said on Thursday. This will make him eligible for selection during the coming tour of South Africa. 

We have today received an official letter from the International Cricket Council (ICC) informing us that Shabbirs 12-month ban has been lifted, PCB director of cricket operations Saleem Altaf said. (Agencies) 




